# Bogey v1 — System Requirements Specification
version: 1.0.0  
status: Locked

---

# 1. Introduction

This document defines the system‑level requirements for **Bogey v1**, the deterministic, reproducible, dataset‑driven artifact lifecycle engine that succeeds **Goblin v1.0.0** and replaces the automation‑heavy behaviors of **Skunk**.

Bogey’s requirements are expressed as **SR‑xxx** items and are implementation‑agnostic, testable, and drift‑proof.

A lineage diagram and version‑control‑style evolution notes appear at the end of this document.

---

# 2. Bogey v1 System Requirements (SR‑001 → SR‑024)

## SR‑001 — Deterministic Startup
Bogey must start deterministically from canonical storage and produce the same environment on every run.

## SR‑002 — Canonical/Sandbox Separation
Canonical artifacts must reside in the dataset; the sandbox must be reconstructable and disposable.

## SR‑003 — No Recursive Scanning
Bogey must not recursively scan directories to discover models, nodes, or workflows.

## SR‑004 — Explicit Artifact Declaration
All artifacts must be explicitly declared via registry, manifest, or user‑initiated Manager download.

## SR‑005 — Symlink‑Only Population
ComfyUI directories must be populated using symlinks only; no large binaries may be copied into the sandbox.

## SR‑006 — No Filesystem Inference
Bogey must not infer meaning from filenames or directory structure; all metadata must be explicit.

## SR‑007 — Registry Metadata Only
The registry must contain metadata only, not binaries.

## SR‑008 — Registry Persistence
The registry must persist across sessions in /kaggle/working.

## SR‑009 — Canonical Is Authoritative
Canonical dataset contents are the authoritative source of truth for all artifacts.

## SR‑010 — Deterministic Reconstruction
Bogey must reconstruct the sandbox deterministically from canonical storage on every startup.

## SR‑011 — No Resurrection Without Data
Missing canonical artifacts are fatal; Bogey must not guess or recreate missing data.

## SR‑012 — Tombstone Preservation
Deleted artifacts must not be resurrected unless explicitly re‑added.

## SR‑013 — Hash Verification
Bogey must compute and verify hashes for all canonical and ingested artifacts.

## SR‑014 — No Filesystem‑Driven Behavior
Bogey must not change behavior based on what happens to be present in the sandbox.

## SR‑015 — No Recursive Model Discovery
Bogey must not search for models or nodes beyond explicitly declared paths.

## SR‑016 — Single‑Pass Recovery
Recovery must run once per startup; a second trigger indicates corruption and must activate the loop‑breaker.

## SR‑017 — Structured Logging
Bogey must emit structured JSON‑lines logs for all recovery, ingestion, and reconstruction events.

## SR‑018 — Read‑Only Introspection API
Bogey must expose a read‑only introspection interface (CLI + Python) for status, logs, diffs, and verification.

## SR‑019 — Disk‑Pressure Warnings
Bogey must emit warnings when /kaggle/working exceeds 90% (soft) and 95% (hard) of quota.

## SR‑020 — Canonical Upstream Acquisition
Bogey may download canonical artifacts from user‑declared upstreams; these downloads must be explicit, logged, and hash‑verified.

## SR‑021 — Manager‑Driven Ingestion
Bogey must ingest artifacts downloaded by ComfyUI‑Manager when initiated explicitly by the user.

## SR‑022 — No Inference‑Based Acquisition
Bogey must not perform workflow‑driven downloads, dependency resolution, or any inference‑based acquisition.

## SR‑023 — No Automatic Updates
Bogey must not detect or install updates to models or nodes.

## SR‑024 — No Environment Automation
Bogey must not install dependencies, repair environments, or bootstrap ComfyUI.

